180
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:13,640
We decided to reflect upon our acts and take footage that can be enjoyed by everyone in front of the screen.

181
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:14,740
Yay.

182
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:16,360
Uh...

183
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:19,010
I won't let you say you're leaving after coming this far.

184
00:11:19,010 --> 00:11:22,440
We already have a contract with the Superintendent that
if we present her with funny footage featuring Hayata-kun,

185
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:26,580
then she'll give us 30% more funding next term.

186
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:27,300
When did you do that?

187
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:32,350
Plus, Nagi-chan agreed to help as a club member.

188
00:11:33,490 --> 00:11:34,910
What's wrong?

189
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:38,150
Anyway, what is this Normal Story Competition?

190
00:11:38,150 --> 00:11:40,410
Thank you for asking, Nagi-pon.

191
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:42,130
You see, Nagi-rin...

192
00:11:42,130 --> 00:11:44,350
...This is how it goes, Nagi Springfield.

193
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:48,250
Um, can you just call me Nagi like normal?

194
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,150
This was back when I was in elementary school.

195
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:50,660
Excuse me...

196
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:54,550
I was at a really rundown fishing village.

197
00:11:55,430 --> 00:11:59,320
That village seemed as though time had stopped.

198
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:08,960
It was pretty creepy at first, but at the inn we stayed at, a really worn out statue of Ninomiya Kinjirou stood facing the ocean.

199
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,900
From what the landlady of the inn said...

200
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:16,810
At night, that statue turns around to make sure no kids staying at this inn are staying up late.

201
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:20,790
So you mustn't stay up too late, okay?

202
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,270
Yeah, I've heard those kinds of stories before.

203
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:27,300
I see. So we're going to gather those common stories.

204
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,670
No!

205
00:12:28,670 --> 00:12:30,360
The story continues.

206
00:12:30,970 --> 00:12:34,190
When you hear something like that, you have to confirm it, right?

207
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:38,820
At night, we snuck out with a few kids to check.

208
00:12:39,210 --> 00:12:41,620
The time was 2 AM.

209
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:44,880
Looking back, we really shouldn't have.

210
00:12:45,130 --> 00:12:46,830
It was pitch dark out.

211
00:12:46,830 --> 00:12:51,720
It was a windy night, too, with a sound like human groaning.

212
00:12:52,350 --> 00:12:54,340
We waited for ten minutes, then twenty minutes.

213
00:12:54,890 --> 00:12:56,920
It was summer, yet it was strangely chilly.

214
00:12:57,770 --> 00:13:01,130
The next moment, we couldn't believe what we saw!

215
00:13:02,970 --> 00:13:06,490
We had all fallen asleep at some point, and morning had come.

216
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:08,900
Whatever happened to the statue of Kinjirou?

217
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:12,480
Everyone was asleep, so no one confirmed it.

218
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:16,900
You used seventeen cuts for that worthless story?!

219
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:22,540
Just like that we collect normal stories where nothing happens that can't be used in any kind of context...

220
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:27,560
...and want to make a collection of footage that makes viewers feel, "Ah, that was a waste of time."

221
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:30,420
We don't need a collection like that.

222
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:36,520
However, all humans have one or two worthless stories like that.

223
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:40,480
Come on. I know you have one, too.

224
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:43,130
A really worthless story that you have sealed away.

225
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:44,590
Well. Um, I...

226
00:13:45,310 --> 00:13:51,250
I used to live in a really crappy house as a kid.

227
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:52,980
You do have one to share?

228
00:13:53,850 --> 00:13:56,190
That house was really crappy.

229
00:13:56,190 --> 00:13:59,720
At night, the windows would always rattle.

230
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,660
One night, I was staying at home alone.

231
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:06,820
At the time, we didn't have electricity, so it was pitch dark inside.

232
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:09,880
I tried to go to bed, curled up in my futon,

233
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,530
but I realized something.

234
00:14:11,940 --> 00:14:16,130
"Hey, the rattling noise is louder than usual."

235
00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:22,950
I was scared, but as though I was drawn by something, I walked towards the window.

236
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:28,270
I slowly opened the curtain,
and took a look outside the window,

237
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:30,050
and I noticed that...

238
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:32,160
...the wind was stronger than usual.

239
00:14:34,390 --> 00:14:36,390
So what?!

240
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:37,890
Nothing happened.

241
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:41,190
But that's exactly what we're looking for.

242
00:14:41,190 --> 00:14:43,220
Good job, Hayata-kun. You know how things go.

243
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:45,230
Thank you.

244
00:14:45,230 --> 00:14:48,540
Yes, yes, yes! I want to tell my story, too!

245
00:14:48,540 --> 00:14:51,220
Katsura-sensei! Where did you come from?

246
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:56,540
At noon, I leave the POD room, right?

247
00:14:56,990 --> 00:15:01,500
One day after work, I felt this
the moment I stepped into the room:

248
00:15:01,950 --> 00:15:03,750
"Something's not right."

249
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:06,340
At first glance, the room hadn't changed.

250
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:11,220
But I could tell that something important was gone.

251
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,490
I thoroughly checked the room.

252
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:19,680
Then I finally realized what I was missing.

253
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:21,130
I was missing...

254
00:15:21,130 --> 00:15:22,050
Missing what?

255
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:24,040
...cash from my wallet!

256
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:28,140
What the heck was that?!

